# utilities-risk вЂ” Server

## Overview

REST API server for the utilities-risk application.

## Stack

| Component | Details    |
| --------- | ---------- |
| Runtime   | .NET 8     |
| Database  | PostgreSQL |
| Cache     | Redis      |

## API

| Method | Path    | Description  |
| ------ | ------- | ------------ |
| GET    | /health | Health check |

## Architecture

Nginx acts as a reverse proxy. All requests to `/api/*` are forwarded to this server on port `5000`.

## Development

The server is started via `docker-compose.yml` alongside the Angular client and Nginx.

```
Client (port 3000) в”Ђв”Ђв”ђ
                     в”њв”Ђв”Ђ> Nginx (port 80) в”Ђв”Ђ> /api/* в†’ Server (port 5000)
                     в”‚
                     в””в”Ђв”Ђ> /     в†’ Client
```

-- Core Tables
trades -- trade_id, instrument, direction, qty, price, trader_id, timestamp
positions -- position_id, instrument, net_qty, avg_price, mtm_value
risk_metrics -- metric_id, position_id, var_1d, cvar, exposure, calculated_at
pnl_snapshots -- snapshot_id, portfolio_id, realized_pnl, unrealized_pnl, timestamp
alerts -- alert_id, type, threshold, status, triggered_at
users -- user_id, email, role, created_at
audit_logs -- log_id, user_id, action, entity, timestamp, ip_address

-- TimescaleDB Hypertables (Time-Series)
market_price_ticks -- instrument_id, price, volume, bid, ask, timestamp (partitioned by time)
risk_metric_history -- position_id, var_value, exposure, timestamp (partitioned by time)

